  <refnamediv>
    <refname>paraview</refname><refpurpose>Visualisation with paraview</refpurpose>
  </refnamediv>



<refsynopsisdiv>
   <title>Calling Sequence</title>
   <synopsis>
   paraview(Var)
   paraview(Var1,Var2,...)
   </synopsis>
</refsynopsisdiv>

<refsection>
   <title>Parameters</title>
   <variablelist>
   <varlistentry><term>Var</term>
      <listitem><para> can be a mesh (tri2d or tet3d) or an element (p1_2d or p1_3d)</para></listitem></varlistentry>
   <varlistentry><term>Var1, Var2 ...</term>
     <listitem><para> Differents elements defining on the same mesh.
   </para></listitem></varlistentry>
   </variablelist>
</refsection>

<refsection>
   <title>Description</title>
   <para>
This function export the variables in VTK file format and call the external software paraview with tthe file in argument (see http://www.paraview.org/).
   </para>
</refsection>

<refsection>
   <title>Examples</title>
   <programlisting role="example"><![CDATA[
th=square2d(20,20) // square mesh with cardinals boundaries "W", "E", "N" and "S"
u=p1(th,'x/(1+x*y/2)')
paraview(u)
   ]]></programlisting>
</refsection>

